Melt butter over low heat and add to 2 cups Basic Cookie Mix. Lightly beat the egg and add to mixture. Stir in vanilla and mix well. With lightly floured hands shape into 1 inch balls and arrange about 2 inches apart on a greased cookie sheet. Bake at 350 degrees F (180 degrees C) for 12 to 15 minutes until golden. Cool a couple of minutes before removing from cookie sheet to racks to complete cooling.